Package us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFrameVector3DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameTuple3DBasics, FrameTuple3DReadOnly, FrameVector3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FrameVector3DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameVector3D
    public interface FixedFrameVector3DBasics
extends FrameVector3DReadOnly, FixedFrameTuple3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DBasics
    Write and read interface for a 3D vector expressed in a constant reference frame, i.e. this vector is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Vector3DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFrameVector3DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on vectors occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FixedFrameVector3DBasics extends Vector3DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Vector3DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFrameVector3DBasics.
